text.tspan: The Barnes Foundation is home to one of the most important
collections of Post-Impressionist and early Modernist art in the
world, and includes masterworks by Cezanne, Renoir, Matisse,
Picasso, Van Gogh, and others. The world-renowned permanent
collection is known not just for the artworks themselves, but for
their presentation in ‘ensembles’—groups of paintings, decorative
art and sculpture that share formal connections.
